 Extra Mural Lecture series 201617

 presents

 'Transparency in Governance and Administration : Challenges Ahead'

 a talk by

 Dr. Kiran Bedi IPS  (retd.)

 Hon'ble Lieutenant Governor of Puducherry

 Date Monday, 8th August

 Venue: Student Activity Center (SAC), IIT Madras

 Time: 5:30 pm onwards

 Speaker Profile:

 Dr Kiran Bedi is a retired Indian Police Service officer,
 Law graduate, social activist, former tennis player and politician. The
 first woman to join the Indian Police Service (IPS), she remained in
 service for 35 years before taking voluntary retirement in 2007 as Direct
or
 General, Bureau of Police Research and Development to focus on social
 activism and writing. In 1993, she was posted to the Delhi Prisons as
 Inspector General (IG) where she introduced several reforms at Tihar Jail
,
 which gained worldwide acclaim and won her the Ramon Magsaysay Award in
 1994. She is an author of several books such as I Dare, It's Always
 Possible etc. She also initiated the establishment of two organisations
 which she runs to date, Navajyoti and the India Vision Foundation for
 improving the lives of drug addicts and various underprivileged people.
 Noted for her several acts of courage and compassion, her life is the
 subject of many documentaries and films.

 You can ask all your questions to Dr. Kiran Bedi. Fill this form
 to get your questions listed in
 Q&A session of 8th August, Monday inaugural lecture.

 First years students can bring mess Cards instead of ID cards for the
 entry.


 Important Instructions:

 1) Please be seated at least 15 minutes before the start of the event.

 2) Avoid carrying mobile phones to the event.

 3) Unauthorized Photography and Videography of the event is strictly
 prohibited.

